recent:
  - date: 2026-06-10
    branch: feature/cran-incoming
    title: "feat: CRAN-incoming hardening — strict check passes + cranlint Tier 4 (v2.3.0)"
    spec: docs/specs/SPEC-cran-incoming-hardening-2026-06-10.md
    state: implemented, PR-ready (gates green)
    summary: |
      r:check --strict runs both Suggests-withholding flavors (check (noSuggests)
      + check (suggests-only)) with --run-donttest; --incoming adds the CRAN
      incoming bundle. r:cran-prep runs the strict passes by default and BLOCKS
      `ready` on failure (behavior change). New pure-stdlib lib/cranlint.py adds
      advisory description/build-hygiene/docs-consistency stages (never block).
      E2E proof: tests/fixtures/suggestbug.{before,after} — noSuggests pass
      catches the medfit 0.2.1 unconditional-Suggests bug class with real R
      (verified live). Gates: pytest 168 + 2 opt-in e2e, test-all.sh 31/31.
      Merged dev (5b3fc17) in to stay current; dev's r:submit v2.5.0 spec carried along.

  - date: 2026-06-10
    branch: dev
    title: "spec + convention: CRAN-incoming hardening (v2.3.0) groundwork"
    state: SUPERSEDED by the implementation entry above
    summary: |
      On dev: established a reusable research+citation convention
      (docs/specs/_TEMPLATE-{SPEC,RESEARCH}.md + README "Research & Citation
      Standard" + 7-step workflow), and promoted the CRAN-incoming proposal to an
      approved SPEC grounded in a cited RESEARCH companion. Research corrected a
      real draft error: the medfit/MASS noSuggests catcher is
      _R_CHECK_DEPENDS_ONLY_, not _R_CHECK_SUGGESTS_ONLY_ (per WRE). Also seeded
      SPEC-r-submit-github-prerelease (v2.5.0) groundwork.
