  - date: 2026-05-11
    pr: 4
    branch: feature/mcp-absorb-rest
    title: "Path B v1.3.0 — finish MCP absorption (B.2 + B.3 + B.4)"
    state: MERGED
    merge_commit: 716dcab
    summary: |
      Completes Path B — `rforge_status` + `rforge_init` ported to `lib/`;
      `rforge-mcp` archive paperwork drafted in `docs/migration/`. After
      this lands, the plugin is fully self-sufficient — no MCP server
      required at runtime for any of the 7 implemented MCP tools.

      Consolidated 3 worktrees → 1 (B.2 + B.3 + B.4 in one atomic PR).

      Scope correction during execution: MCP's `status` tool was a thin
      .STATUS reader, NOT the 4-mode contract the SPEC implied. ported
      faithfully; 4-mode design descoped to v1.4.0 (backlog).

      Pre-merge review caught 6 concerns; all addressed in commit
      14c37de (rebased SHA) before merge:
        - error handling consistency in init_context
        - format_text test_status column
        - 3× type:ignore cleanup via `is not None` narrowing
        - frozen=True on InitResult, __all__ added, blocking_issues None semantics
        - datetime isoformat consistency
        - .STATUS regex parser format coupling documented

      Final state: 65/65 pytest, 23/23 test-all.sh.

      Post-merge cross-repo work pending: archive data-wise/rforge-mcp
      on GitHub (paperwork drafted in docs/migration/, executes manually).

  - date: 2026-05-10
    pr: 3
    branch: feature/mcp-absorb-discovery
    title: "feat: Path B Phase B.1 — port discovery + deps to lib/"
    state: MERGED
    merge_commit: 951e055
    summary: |
      First Path B port. Three of rforge-mcp's tools (rforge_detect,
      rforge_deps, rforge_impact) now live as pure-Python modules in
      lib/. Plugin commands invoke them directly via `python3 -m lib.X`.
      Non-breaking: existing rforge-mcp users keep all functionality.

      Includes pre-PR self-review refactor (commit 5d95c7a) addressing
      2 blockers caught in review:
        - lib/ made a real Python package (was sys.path hack risking
          name collision)
        - assert → walrus operator in parse_description (assert is
          strippable under python -O)

      Final state: 36/36 pytest, 23/23 test-all.sh, public API
      unchanged. Pre-merge ORCHESTRATE-*.md removal per CLAUDE.md
      merge-cleanup rule (commit e37a6a9).

      Lines: +2335/-194 across 21 files (lib/__init__.py, discovery.py
      361 lines, deps.py 481 lines, 3 test files, 5 doc pages,
      scripts/gen_lib_reference.py, command updates).

